value.0: This hulking Orc looks very intimidating. His battle-torn look is shrouded in a strange wise aura for one of his race. Those around him seem to revere him as some sort of living legend.

Once known as the "Tiny Scourge", this Goblin was the first to ally with King Wolfpelt before we released the larger Monsters from captivity. His grim attire, dried blood on his face and trophy of a Troll that stood in his way leads you to believe this Goblin is a threat.

This Grey Kobold sponsors a muscular build. However, the most surprising fact is that, for those keen on Kobold voices, this is a female Kobold. Somehow, this Matriarch has gained control over the Kobold tribe as a warrior.

A fine stringed instrument, a lute is very mobile, and as such, a favorite of traveling minstrels everywhere.  It has a pleasing sound, as the strings musical vibrations echo in the hollow wooden chamber and reverberate.
This sturdy blacksmith's anvil bears the dented sheen of long use. Something in you wonders what great weapons and armor have been shaped upon its well-worn surface.
There is nothing special about this object.
The spears lean into the wooden rack, waiting for release.

This strange pillar seems hand-carved by some kind of claw. It reads in Draconic:

"I am sorry I was unable to save you.

Till we meet again."
You can take a tiny chip of this crystal and use it as a lens in your porting wand.
Seems like King Wolfpelt stole himself something wonderous.
